<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Import from IFC and FBX</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Import from IFC and FBX</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> allows importing </text><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">.ifc</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">.fbx</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> models.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">.ifc </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">files designed to store 3D sources are supported by most of programs in the architecture, engineering, and construction (AEC) industry. &#160;It is widely used as collaboration format in Building Information Modeling (BIM) based projects. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">.fbx</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> format is used in:</text></para>
    <list id="13" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullet_1" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">3ds Max</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">Blender</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Rhinoceros-for-Windows" styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">Rhinoceros</link></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">Maya</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">Cinema 4D</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">Revit LT</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.ifc is widely promoted by Autodesk and is used by Solibri. Note that the latter does not strictly observe the IFC requirements, therefore issues may occur during data export from Solibri to </text><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> (we support the strict format). </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Procedure Heading"><text styleclass="Procedure Heading" translate="true">To import an .ifc/.fbx file:</text></para>
    <list id="14" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Procedure" style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Procedure"><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true">Create an empty project and open it in </text><var styleclass="Procedure">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true">. You can use an existing project, if it is ok to append .</text><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">ifc/.fbx</text><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true"> content to it, or to overwrite existing content. </text></li>
    </list>
    <list id="15" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Procedure" style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Procedure"><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true">Choose </text><text styleclass="GUI_item" translate="true">Project</text><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true"> &gt; </text><text styleclass="GUI_item" translate="true">Import</text><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true"> in </text><var styleclass="Procedure">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true"> top menu.</text></li>
    </list>
    <list id="14" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Procedure" style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Procedure"><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true">Find the necessary file by using Windows Explorer and click </text><text styleclass="GUI_item" translate="true">Open</text><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true">.</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:center;"><image src="ifc_fbx.png" scale="60.00%" width="634" height="485" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
    <list id="14" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Procedure" style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Procedure"><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true">Define your export options in the standard </text><var styleclass="Procedure">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true"> export dialog that displays.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Procedure"><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="GUI_item" translate="true">OK</text><text styleclass="Procedure" translate="true">.</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">When a </text><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> project is created, it is no longer connected with its original IFC or FBX model. If you do changes in </text><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, they cannot be synced back to the file. However, if you make changes in the original model, you can always do re-export to &quot;current project&quot; (see the description above).</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The dialog box also has an option to duplicate back faces. </text><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> only shows the front face of the surface, so when you look at it from the back, it is invisible. If the model assumes two-sided surfaces but only has one-sided, then you may want to select this option. However, it duplicates every surface of the scene thereby increasing its size and slowing down the performance.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading 2"><text styleclass="Heading 2" translate="true">Note on Lighting Sources</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> Editor doesn not allow creating new light sources. All light sources that you want to be in the project should be created in the software you use. </text><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%BRAND_NAME%&gt;</var><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> should detect all the light source information automatically when importing your project. </text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
